The basic idea of logistic regression is to use the mechanism already developed for linear regression by modeling the probability p using a linear predictor function, i.e. a linear combination of the explanatory variables and a set of regression coefficients that are specific to the model at hand but the same for all trials. The linear predictor function for a particular data point i is written as:

