A closely related model assumes that each i is associated not with a single Bernoulli trial but with n independent identically distributed trials, where the observation Y is the number of successes observed (the sum of the individual Bernoulli-distributed random variables), and hence follows a binomial distribution:

An example of this distribution is the fraction of seeds (p ) that germinate after n are planted.

